        <div class="col-md-6  order-1 order-md-2" style="font-family:'Pacifico', cursive;color:#e5eff7;">
            <h1 class="mt-4 text-center">What you’ll need:</h1>
            <p class="mt-3 px-5" >
                <ul class="px-5  py-3">
                    <li>14g (approximately 7 teaspoons) coffee in coarse, channi grind.</li>
                    <li>Channi / Strainer.</li>
                    <li>140ml water (½ cup + 1 tablespoon) at 94°C (approximately 1:50 minutes off the boil).</li>
                    <li>One Cup.</li>
                    <li>Muslin cloth, if possible.</li>
                    <li>One Kettle.</li>
                    <li>Scales, if possible, otherwise follow eye measurements.</li>

                </ul>        
            </p>

        </div> 

       </div>

   </div>
   <div class="container-fluid">
       <div class="row">
        
        <div class="col-lg-6  " style="font-family:'Pacifico', cursive;color:#e5eff7;">
            <h1 class="mt-5 text-center">Brewing Recipe</h1>
            <p class="mt-3 px-5" >
                <ul class="px-5  py-3">
                    <li>Add 14g coffee to your cup.</li>
                    <li>Add 130ml hot water. </li>
                    <li>Leave for 4 minutes.</li>
                    <li>At 4 minutes, stir 10 times. </li>
                    <li>Pour brew through channi into another cup. </li>
                    <li>Add more of the remaining hot water, or milk to your preference.</li>

                </ul>        
            </p>

        </div> 
